{
  "stem": "13096.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I was trying, I was thinking I will do something for the humanity.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not aware of what's happening in Europe.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not aware of the program because you know, half of the-- of the Jewish population were-- you know, had a-- a radio to listen to.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were just reading, just the local newspaper.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They never say anything about those things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only thing we-- we heard vaguely, through the Jewish movement you know, that we have-- we were receiving from Italy, that the-- the German was in power, you know, like Hitler, and he was a bad man, and we shouldn't buy products from Germany.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we used to go to the-- when we were at school, and we used to go and buy pencils and-- and paper and all this, we were avoiding, like, things made in Germany.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like Faber, for-- for instance, it was our-- our pencil that we used to do our school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was always Faber, the name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But since we heard those things, you know, bad about him, we avoid buying those products from Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is the only thing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Otherwise, life was going on.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the-- the-- the-- the Italians were very friendly as usual.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was no incident.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were lots of intermarriages, assimilation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That means the Italians, as a matter of fact, fancy more the Jewish girl than the other one, but it was the religious beliefs that kept her, you know, to assimilating more.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was to start with, you know, not about anti-Semitism or whatever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our life start to change when the war started.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because we-- we start feeling the-- the restrictions of buying the food and the clothes and everything.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
